<subSubSection id="11D26523454FB64DB5C5F945FDEA1A4A" pageId="12" pageNumber="471" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="597736A8454FB64DB5C5F945FDEA1A4A" blockId="12.[151,1436,1744,1843]" pageId="12" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA454FB64DB5C5F945FEB01B92" bold="true" box="[151,269,1744,1770]" pageId="12" pageNumber="471">Remarks:</emphasis>
The occurrence in the 
<collectingRegion id="9B0CF84A454FB64DB743F945FDDE1B92" box="[529,611,1744,1770]" country="Ukraine" name="Crimea" pageId="12" pageNumber="471">Crimea</collectingRegion>
was published by 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B59454FB64DB667F944FBBF1B93" author="Martynova, O. M." box="[821,1026,1744,1771]" pageId="12" pageNumber="471" pagination="721 - 747" refId="ref15684" refString="Martynova, O. M. (1957) Skopionnitsy (Mecoptera) fauny SSSR. II Semeistvo Panorpidae. [Scorpion-flies (Mecoptera) of USSR fauna. II The family Panorpidae]. Entomologicheskoe obozrenie, 36 (3), 721 - 747. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1957">Martynova (1957)</bibRefCitation>
and repeated by 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B59454FB64DB190F945FE8A1A76" author="Dorokhova, G. I. &amp; Martynova, O. M." pageId="12" pageNumber="471" pagination="97 - 107" refId="ref13398" refString="Dorokhova, G. I. &amp; Martynova, O. M. (1987) Otryad Mecoptera. Skorpionovye mukhi. [The order Mecoptera. Scorpion-flies. Key of the insects of the European part of SSSR]. Opredelitel nasekomykh Evropeiskoi chasti SSSR, 4 (VI), 97 - 107. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1987">Dorokhova &amp; Martynova (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. As 
<bibRefCitation id="3D594B59454FB64DB437F961FD991A77" author="Willmann, R." box="[357,548,1780,1807]" pageId="12" pageNumber="471" pagination="543 - 564" refId="ref17121" refString="Willmann, R. (1975) Die Gattung Panorpa in der Turkei. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, 79, 543 - 564." type="journal article" year="1975">Willmann (1975)</bibRefCitation>
stated, 
<taxonomicName id="9EC84D2B454FB64DB72BF960FCA41A76" authorityName="Hagen" authorityYear="1863" box="[633,793,1781,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Panorpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mecoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="471" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picta">
<emphasis id="6BBCEABA454FB64DB72BF960FCA41A76" box="[633,793,1781,1806]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="471">Panorpa picta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a nomen dubium, and the data from 
<collectingRegion id="9B0CF84A454FB64DB19BF961FAA61A76" box="[1225,1307,1780,1806]" country="Ukraine" name="Crimea" pageId="12" pageNumber="471">Crimea</collectingRegion>
are unclear because they are based on females only.
</paragraph>
